{
  "A Venn diagram uses overlapping circles to show:": "",
  "Individual data points collected during a statistical experiment or survey": "",
  "Relationships between sets, including intersections and unions": "",
  "The mean and median of a quantitative data set computed from observations": "",
  "Time series data that tracks changes in a variable over successive periods": "",
  "Venn diagrams visually represent set relationships: union (A or B), intersection (A and B), and complement (not A).": "",
  "The overlapping region of two circles in a Venn diagram represents:": "",
  "A intersection B (A and B)": "",
  "A union B": "",
  "A complement": "",
  "The empty set": "",
  "The overlap contains elements that belong to BOTH sets A and B.": "",
  "If two circles in a Venn diagram do not overlap, the events are:": "",
  "Complementary": "",
  "Identical": "",
  "Independent": "",
  "Mutually exclusive": "",
  "No overlap means the events have no common outcomes, which is the definition of mutually exclusive.": "",
  "In a Venn diagram, A ∪ B (A union B) represents:": "",
  "Only the overlap": "",
  "Only the non-overlapping parts": "",
  "Everything outside A and B": "",
  "Everything in A, B, or both": "",
  "The union includes all elements that are in A, in B, or in both A and B.": "",
  "The region outside both circles but inside the rectangle represents:": "",
  "The sample space, which includes every possible outcome of the experiment": "",
  "A intersection B, the set of elements belonging to both A and B simultaneously": "",
  "Neither A nor B (complement of A ∪ B)": "",
  "A union B, the set of elements that belong to either A or B or both sets": "",
  "The rectangle is the universal set (sample space). The area outside both circles represents elements not in A or B.": "",
  "In a survey of 100 people, 60 like chocolate, 45 like vanilla, and 25 like both. Using a Venn diagram, how many like chocolate only?": "",
  "25": "",
  "45": "",
  "35": "",
  "60": "",
  "Chocolate only = Total chocolate − Both = 60 − 25 = 35.": "",
  "Using the survey above (100 people, 60 chocolate, 45 vanilla, 25 both), how many like neither?": "",
  "30": "",
  "0": "",
  "20": "",
  "Total in union = 35 + 25 + 20 = 80 (choc only + both + vanilla only). Neither = 100 − 80 = 20.": "",
  "A Venn diagram with three overlapping circles has how many distinct regions (including the area outside all circles)?": "",
  "6": "",
  "7": "",
  "9": "",
  "8": "",
  "Three overlapping circles create 7 regions inside the circles plus 1 region outside all three = 8 total regions.": "",
  "If P(A) = 0.5, P(B) = 0.4, and P(A ∩ B) = 0.2, then P(A ∪ B) from the Venn diagram is:": "",
  "0.2": "",
  "1.1": "",
  "0.7": "",
  "0.9": "",
  "P(A ∪ B) = P(A) + P(B) − P(A ∩ B) = 0.5 + 0.4 − 0.2 = 0.7.": "",
  "De Morgan's Law states that the complement of (A ∪ B) equals:": "",
  "A ∩ B": "",
  "A' ∪ B'": "",
  "A' ∩ B'": "",
  "(A ∪ B)'  is undefined": "",
  "De Morgan's Law: (A ∪ B)' = A' ∩ B'. Not being in A or B means being outside A AND outside B.": "",
  "What is a Venn diagram?": "",
  "A bar chart showing set sizes as vertical bars for easy comparison between groups": "",
