  "What does 'symmetric difference' mean?": "",
  "The union of A and B": "",
  "All elements in both A and B": "",
  "The set of elements in either A or B but NOT in both, written A △ B": "",
  "The intersection of A and B": "",
  "The symmetric difference A △ B = (A ∪ B) − (A ∩ B), which is the union minus the intersection.": "",
  "In a gym of 150 members, 90 do cardio, 70 do weights, and 40 do both. A Venn diagram is drawn. How many do only cardio, only weights, and neither?": "",
  "Only cardio = 50, Only weights = 30, Neither = 40": "",
  "Only cardio = 50, Only weights = 30, Neither = 30": "",
  "Only cardio = 40, Only weights = 40, Neither = 30": "",
  "Only cardio = 90, Only weights = 70, Neither = 0": "",
  "Only cardio = 90−40 = 50. Only weights = 70−40 = 30. Union = 50+40+30 = 120. Neither = 150−120 = 30.": "",
  "A school has 200 students. 120 study math, 80 study science, 100 study English. 50 study math and science, 60 study math and English, 30 study science and English, and 20 study all three. How many study at least one subject?": "",
  "160": "",
  "300": "",
  "180": "",
  "200": "",
  "By inclusion-exclusion: |M∪S∪E| = 120+80+100−50−60−30+20 = 180.": "",
  "From the school above, how many study none of the three subjects?": "",
  "80": "",
  "40": "",
  "None = 200 − 180 = 20 students study none of the three subjects.": "",
  "A tech company surveyed 300 employees. 200 use Slack, 150 use Teams, and 100 use both. What is P(Slack or Teams) for a randomly selected employee?": "",
  "250/300 = 5/6": "",
  "350/300": "",
  "100/300": "",
  "200/300": "",
  "P(S ∪ T) = P(S) + P(T) − P(S ∩ T) = 200/300 + 150/300 − 100/300 = 250/300 = 5/6.": "",
  "Events A and B are such that P(A) = 0.6, P(B) = 0.3, and A and B are mutually exclusive. What does the Venn diagram look like?": "",
